description: Dimensions: L 173.5mm; We 74.9mm; Wbt 25.5mm; Bfg. 32.7mm; Bst (middle) 29.3mm; Tsep 7.7mm; Wt. 590.9 gms,Typology: slightly irregular bev. across fg. tops on sep.; one sep. little wider than other - both curved between in cross-sec., with rounded angles; fg. and stop crests neat rounded - no distinct bevels; stops little depressed in centre; short fg. extensions onto bl. with flattened crests tending to splay at bases; midribs low-rounded bumps with at crisp bevels - one extends virt. to edge bev., other higher, but as short as fg. extensions; slides slightly bowed in cross-sec.,Manufacture: cg. fl. remains as very broad low rounded bump - less pronounced on other side, virt. all trace removed on bl. sides, with some hammer rippling; dimples generally over surface - hammer marks or moulding? collection: Collection of Dr. A. Relph,Sold at Sotheby's June 7, 1936,Lot 38 (sold for 4-5-0)
description: Except for notches chipped out of the edges, in perfect condition: These notches are regular + V shaped + have been made in ancient times, the notch on the inner side of them is of the same dark brown patina as the sword. They have the appearance of having been made deliberately.  Nine rivet holes: three down centre of hilt, three on each shoulder. The midrib of blade continues in the form of a pointed elevation up to the lowest rivet hole in the hilt. Edges of hilt are flanged and two flanges run (from top of hilt, nearly to its face) between the side flanges + the rivet holes. In addition, the two smaller flanges run between these two, for the distance between the uppermost rivet hole + the top of the hilt.
remarks: "B.25 R. Thames" in white ink by ricasso notches.
